TSHWANE - Three children and one adult were killed in a collision along the N14 near the Wierda onramp in Centurion on Saturday afternoon. According to ER24 spokesperson Shaun Herbst, the collision occurred at approximately 2 pm on Saturday afternoon. READ: One dead, 15 injured in horrific Durban crash One vehicle was severely damaged and all the occupants were ejected from the car during the crash. Three young children and an adult were killed in the collision. Two women from the same vehicle were transported to a nearby hospital for treatment of moderate injuries. The male driver from the second vehicle sustained moderate injuries. He was assessed and treated on the scene before being transported to a nearby hospital for care. The exact circumstances surrounding this collision is not yet known. Local authorities attended the scene and will conduct an investigation.